# Alembic Migrations Guide

This directory contains database migration scripts for the payment service.

## Commands

### Generate a New Migration

After making changes to your SQLAlchemy models, generate a new migration:

```bash
poetry run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply Migrations

To apply all pending migrations:

```bash
poetry run alembic upgrade head
```

To apply a specific migration:

```bash
poetry run alembic upgrade <revision_id>
```

### Rollback Migrations

To rollback to the previous migration:

```bash
poetry run alembic downgrade -1
```

To rollback to a specific migration:

```bash
poetry run alembic downgrade <revision_id>
```

To rollback to the initial state (no migrations):

```bash
poetry run alembic downgrade base
```

### View Migration History

```bash
poetry run alembic history
```

### View Current Migration Status

```bash
poetry run alembic current
```

### View Migration Details

To see the SQL that will be executed without actually running it:

```bash
poetry run alembic upgrade head --sql
```

## Important Notes

- This project uses SQLAlchemy Async, so migrations run with async support
- The database URL is configured in `alembic.ini`
- Model metadata is imported from `app.infrastructure.database.base.Base`
- Always review generated migrations before committing
- Never edit existing migration files - create new ones instead